value.text: base64 hashed/salted serial identifier; different from human-readable username
Located from the source of the HTML page by searching the source for string: itemprop="channelId"

The following command (when replacing CHANNELNAME) can be used on typical Linux distributions to extract the required channel ID to use for this property from a YouTube channel's URL that contains a channel name rather than channel ID: curl --no-progress-meter 'https://www.youtube.com/c/CHANNELNAME' | xmllint --html --recover --nowarning --xpath 'string(//meta[@itemprop="channelId"]/@content)' - 2>/dev/null

To obtain the URL, open the HTML source of the channel page and search for the <link rel="canonical"> tag. The human-readable username can be added as a "YouTube handle" (P11245) qualifier, and the title of the channel can be provided with the "object stated as" (P1932) qualifier.
پتے ڈھونڈݨ لئی Ctrl-I بٹن چھوہو تے کھوج دے حصے وچ canonical پا لاؤ۔ اوتھے link ٹیگ چ شناخت دا پتہ ہندا اے۔ P11245 نال اوہ ورتنوالے دا ناں پا سکدے او۔

Pour obtenir l'URL exact d'une page Youtube, y faire un clic droit, sélectionner "Code source de la page", puis rechercher avec CTRL+F le tag <link rel="canonical" href=". L'identifiant est une suite de chiffres et de lettres.
